What you need to know:

The board held a crisis meeting on Friday as Mr Oimeke carried on with his duties at his desk.By evening, Mr Oimeke was still making calls to staff members to present the monthly pump prices’ statement for his signature, unaware that they had been instructed not to give the monthly statement to the embattled boss. By Monday evening, the renewable energy expert was still fighting to stay in office after spending a night in the Ethics and Anti-Corruption Commission cells.